This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the concept of treewidth, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The Erdős-Posa theorem, which is mentioned in the abstract, is a classic result in graph theory and is often studied in the context of graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
